This is with v4.102. Verilates fine without --protect-lib

Given the following example:
```
typedef struct packed {

    logic           a;
    logic  [31:0]   b;
    logic  [31:0]   c;
    logic           d;
    logic           e;
    logic  [ 7:0]   f;
    logic  [63:0]   g;
    logic           h;

} DBG_CPU;
```

if --protect-lib could just convert struct I/Os to the equivilent multi-bit wire port, that would be sufficient for the instancing module to connect that port directly to a struct of the same type (this works with VCS and Xcelium)

If this is simply an accepted limitation of --protect-lib, maybe it could be listed in the documentation
